<html>
<title>Robert G. Blatz - Heritage</title>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<h3>Robert G. Blatz</h3>
<hr><b> Vice President of Administration and Chief Financial Officer</b>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/blatz.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
	 Robert G. Blatz  oversees the foundation's day-to-day financial operations as well as its administrative, computer services, personnel, accounting and payroll departments and assists with the investment and management of the foundation's invested funds. From May 1993 to June 1996, Blatz served as chief of staff to Heritage President Edwin Feulner. 
<p>
	 Before joining Heritage, Blatz served in the U.S. Army as a company commander stationed in Italy. Blatz received several awards for his distinguished service, including the MacArthur Leadership Award and the Meritorious Service Medal for outstanding achievement. 
<P>	Blatz earned a  bachelor's degree in general engineering (with a concentration in economics) from the U.S. Military Academy at West Point, N.Y. He is pursuing masters' degrees in legislative affairs and business administration from George Washington University in Washington, D.C.  He lives in Burke, Va. with his wife Shelly and their daughter Samantha. 
<p>


