<TITLE> The Washington Watch : Congressional Testimony </TITLE>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/townhall/FRC/wash.gif" WIDTH=425 HEIGHT=125>
<H2> Congressional Testimony</H2>
<HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 50%>
<IMG SRC="/townhall/work.gif"WIDTH=40 HEIGHT=40><p>
<B> This Site is Still Under Construction</B> 

</CENTER>
<P>

<P>
<P>
FRC's staff of public policy experts -- and extramural family experts recommended by FRC -- are frequently called to testify before Congressional committees debating pending legislation or seeking guidance on vital family issues.  FRC also routinely submits unsolicited testimony to House and Senate Committees open to informed public opinion.  Topics range from the mundane and technical to the speculative and controversial.  Congressional testimony represents one of FRC's prime educational functions as a nonprofit organization located in the nation's capital.
<UL> 
<LI><A HREF = "/townhall/FRC/donodoc.html">Testimony on the nomination of Dr. Henry W. Foster</A>, Canadite for US Surgeon General

