<html>
<title>Mary Anne Carter - Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">



<h3>MARY ANNE CARTER</h3>
<hr><b>DIRECTOR, CONGRESSIONAL RELATIONS/U.S. SENATE</b>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/carter.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10><p>

	Mary Anne Carter brings extensive campaign and Capitol Hill experience to The Heritage Foundation. Prior to joining Heritage, she actively participated in several prominent campaigns. Most recently, she served as Director of Research for the Dole for President primary campaign where she supervised, coordinated and directed all research on campaign-related issues. 
<p>
	In 1994, Carter successfully helped elect Fred Thompson to the United States Senate. She developed the earned media strategy for the campaign, oversaw debate preparation and directed all campaign research. She later served as Senator Thompson's Legislative Aide to the Judiciary Committee. She also served as campaign manager to then-Congressman Jon Kyl in 1992 and previously worked in the Senate office of the late John Heinz of Pennsylvania.  
<p>
	Carter also worked as a Senior Analyst at the National Republican Senatorial Committee.  She frequently serves as a guest speaker at George Washington University's  Political Management School.  Carter hails from Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. She moved to the nation's capitol after studying political science at West Virginia University.
<p>
<BR><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B29-51</DOCNO>
