<TR>	<TD>Heritage Foundation</td>  <td>leading conservative think-tank</TD>		  <TD>2.1</TD>		  <TD>15</TD>
<TR><TD>23.	Dick Cheney</TD>	  <TD>former defense secretary</TD>		  <td>1.9</td>		  <TD>14</TD>
<TR><TD>	Pete du Pont</TD>	  <TD>former Delaware governor</TD>		  <TD>1.9</TD>		  <TD>14</TD>
<TR><TD>	Ed Feulner	</TD>	  <TD>Heritage Foundation president</TD>		  <TD>1.9</TD>		  <TD>14</TD>
<TR>	<TD>Dick Lugar</TD>		  <TD>Indiana senator</TD>			  <TD>1.9</tD>		  <TD>14</td>
</table>
<P>
<BR>

<I>The data were compiled by Tom Howard and based on 722 responses to the question: "Which 
public policy leader do you most respect?"  Supporters could name more than one answer.</I>
